name: Rental unit in London · ★4.88 · Studio · 2 beds · 1 bath
description:
Spacious & open plan boho warehouse studio apartment in the heart of happening Hackney. Perfect short stay for solo guests & couples, whether working, or on a leisure trip. Great value private flat with a separate entrance.
One of London's most colourful areas. City & West End 30 minutes by train. Great local bars and restaurants within a few minutes walk.
Potentially available for longer periods.

The space
Open plan studio apartment

Guest access
Plenty of public transport options by bus and overground rail.

Nearest trains are Hackney Central Overground (zone 2) which is just 10 mins walk away due south, then 2 stops west to Highbury Islington (Victoria line tube). or 2 stops east to Stratford (Central, Jubillee, and DLR)

Or Hackney Downs overground is also less than 10 minutes south west and 2 stops from Liverpool Street Overground main terminus (Central/Circle/Hammersmith & City tubes).

There
neighborhood_overview: East London is the creative side of the city. Hackney is a unique area of London. It is full of all kinds of life. It is also economically and ethnically diverse. That is part of its charm and character.
host_about:
Film maker, musician, and traveller... 

I've lived in Hackney in east London for over 20 years, and I still delight in the area.  I would encourage anybody to visit this side of London…it's the alternative side, like Kruezberg in Berlin, Williamsburg in NYC, or Christiania in Copenhagen. There's elements of all of those in Hackney. 

I try and travel somewhere exotic once a year or so, ideally with a film-making purpose attached. 

I've been Airbnb'ing for over 10 years, I've met some amazing guests and think it's on the whole a fantastic and worthwhile community.

neighborhood_overview:
A short walk from the buzzing markets of Camden, the tranquility of Hampstead Heath and Regents Park, not to mention the zoo and areas like Hampstead and Primrose Hill on the doorstep.

host_about:
I am an actor and my wife Victoria is a primary school teacher, so we have lots of holiday time to fill with our twin daughters Willow and Eliza (aged 4) and little boy Cosmo (6 months).  

We love theatre (Jerusalem, Complicite, RSC, Cheek by Jowel), film (The Lives of Others, There Will be Blood, Amelie), music (Nick Drake, Bon Iver, John Martyn), good food (I love curry and Vicky loves Japanese), walking and exploring!

We adore travel - Geoffrey's travelled the world for over 2 years and Vicky's worked abroad.  We got engaged in  the Catskills (upstate New York) and married in San Gimignano (Tuscany).  Favourite travel destination, probably Hampi in India - or New York where Geoffrey studied acting.

We love to host and have a private self contained apartment with garden in central London listed on airbnb...we love to give tips about London and being from Scotland and North Yorkshire can give tips on the rest of the country too...
 
Hope to hear from you and look forward to hosting you or staying with you!

Best wishes

Geoffrey, Victoria, Cosmo, Willow and Eliza x

neighborhood_overview:
Barons Court is situated in West London, within the Borough of Hammersmith & Fulham. It is close to the River Thames (with a 17th century River Pub), the Queen’s Club is only 40 to 50 meters away which holds the annual LTA Tennis Championship before Wimbledon. There is a very unique theatre on the same road in a friendly pub. West Kensington/Barons Court is primarily a residential area consisting mainly of Victorian terraced houses, many of which are subdivided into flats. There are excellent examples of Victorian architecture, with several houses and some entire streets listed.
West Kensington/Barons Court is a cosmopolitan enclave, with significant local population diversity.
Local business consists of small shops, offices and restaurants, with the Olympia Exhibition Centre nearby. Indeed, it is the mix of local shops that give the area its character.

neighborhood_overview:
We live in one of the coolest area’s of central London- Brixton. Famous for the Jamaican community and world class music venues including the Brixton Academy.
As you exit the underground you will likely be greeted by the sound of Caribbean steel drum bands busking on the high street and there is always something on offer for those who enjoy people watching!

We are walking distance from the most amazing market culture in the city. The vibe is young, integrated and very friendly with a strong sense of community.

A 15 minute walk or 10 minutes on the bus brings you to Brixton Village Market, the best and biggest permanent indoor pop up street food place in London. The original covered market place has been re appropriated for use as a network of small restaurants, bars and cafe’s making every type of food imaginable from around the world. Lunches are cheap delicious and chilled; evening’s and weekends find Brixton Village Market a location in itself with

host_about:
Greetings from the Veeve team!


Veeve manage the largest collection of homes to rent for short stays in London since 2011, launching in Paris in 2017. Our rental homes are predominantly privately-owned, lived-in homes in vibrant neighbourhoods. Thanks to our fully managed service, when you stay in a Veeve property you can benefit from the spaciousness, personal style and relaxed feel of a home – but with all the amenities of a hotel.


Once a booking is confirmed our Customer Service team will become your main point of contact and get in touch with you to organise your arrival at the property (including airport transfers, upon request); after which our on-the-ground management team will look after all aspects of your stay, with in-stay support available to help with any queries.


We have strict cleanliness guidelines for our cleaners and all staff who enter our properties and have reinforced existing cleaning procedures in line with official WHO, British and French government guidance.


As always, our team ensure that all properties are cleaned to a professional standard before and after each stay, with increased focus on touch-point cleaning (door handles, kitchen surfaces, kettles, taps etc.).

 All staff who enter properties will follow the below procedures:
 

- Carry and regularly use alcohol-based hand rub
- Sanitise their mobile phones 
- Focus extra attention when cleaning key touch-point areas (door handles, kitchen surfaces, kettles, taps etc.)
- Wear protective gear where appropriate
- Wash and disinfect work shoes


We might be able to arrange for property viewings, upon request, for stays of over 28 nights. 

Please be aware once a booking is confirmed you will be required to complete a Rental Agreement and also  ID verification via our partners Superhog. This is mandatory for all our stays and in accordance to short lets requirements with Veeve.

If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact us and we will be sure to answer you promptly.

description:
Modern London one bedroom apartment with great transport links in an enviable location

The space
A newly renovated top floor apartment with Balcony. The apartnent is bright and airy and bennefits from a king sized master bedroom, bathroom wirh full bath and shower unit as well as a large open plan Kitchen and Dinning area. There is a large Sofabed in the living area for additional guests if required.

Guest access
Guests have access to the whole apartment and are welcome to use everything they need. We ask that guests are welcome to use all kitchen appliances available but we ask if you use things, please return them as they were found. With regards to food items, you're welcome to use the fridge and freezer during your stay but please make sure that you take away items with you on departure. We ask the garden/outdoor patio area to only be used up to 10pm so as to respect noise levels for our neighbours.

Other things to note
neighborhood_overview:
Peckham area is undoubtedly one of the greenest and most welcoming areas in the whole of London.


Only a few doors down on Gowlett road is arguably one of London's most honest and best pubs 'The Gowlett'. If you fancy experiencing a local pub with a great sense of community or simply fancy a game of bar billiards then the Gowlett is for you.


Within a few minutes walking distance you are spoilt for choice when it comes to coffee shops and places to eat. Just a minute away you've the choice between more traditional Uplands Cafe or the Trendy South East Cakery are Cafe, a White Rabbit Favourite. The East Dulwich Picture House and Cafe is also well worth a visit just 8 minutes walk and found on Lordship Lane. Here you'll find your main high street stores, supermarkets and eateries mixed with delightful local stores and independents. If you fancy amazing traditional British pub food then try The White Horse, famous for its Sunday Roast and just off Peckham
host_about: Hello. We are a small team of dancers and artists that specialise in the creative industries, working with amazing people and unique individual homes. Our mission is to make sure that both guests and hosts have the best possible experience of sharing their homes. All the properties we list here are cleaned and prepared by our team before arrival with fresh linen and towels provided during each stay.  We do our best to always have someone to meet you at the apartment to hand over the keys and and offer advice and guidance about the local area. We like to keep the lines of communication open so my team and I are always a message or call away. When we're not busy with Property Management, we love to take some time out to enjoy this lovely city. Favourite places are the Royal Opera House and the Serpentine Lido in Hyde Park. We love to dance and seeing shows in the west end is one of the highlights for the team of being in London. We like to travel in style but are equally happy up a mountain or in the country as we are in the city. We love to get lost and explore new places by simply soaking up the atmosphere.

neighborhood_overview:
Peckham area is undoubtedly one of the greenest and most welcoming areas in the whole of London.


Only a few doors down on Gowlett road is arguably one of London's most honest and best pubs 'The Gowlett'. If you fancy experiencing a local pub with a great sense of community or simply fancy a game of bar billiards then the Gowlett is for you.


Within a few minutes walking distance you are spoilt for choice when it comes to coffee shops and places to eat. Just a minute away you've the choice between more traditional Uplands Cafe or the Trendy South East Cakery are Cafe, a White Rabbit Favourite. The East Dulwich Picture House and Cafe is also well worth a visit just 8 minutes walk and found on Lordship Lane. Here you'll find your main high street stores, supermarkets and eateries mixed with delightful local stores and independents. If you fancy amazing traditional British pub food then try The White Horse, famous for its Sunday Roast and just off Peckham
host_about: Hello. We are a small team of dancers and artists that specialise in the creative industries, working with amazing people and unique individual homes. Our mission is to make sure that both guests and hosts have the best possible experience of sharing their homes. All the properties we list here are cleaned and prepared by our team before arrival with fresh linen and towels provided during each stay.  We do our best to always have someone to meet you at the apartment to hand over the keys and and offer advice and guidance about the local area. We like to keep the lines of communication open so my team and I are always a message or call away. When we're not busy with Property Management, we love to take some time out to enjoy this lovely city. Favourite places are the Royal Opera House and the Serpentine Lido in Hyde Park. We love to dance and seeing shows in the west end is one of the highlights for the team of being in London. We like to travel in style but are equally happy up a mountain or in the country as we are in the city. We love to get lost and explore new places by simply soaking up the atmosphere.

Kennington is excellently placed for some of the best cultural experiences in the Capital. It’s a mere 15-minute walk to the South Bank, the heartland of The Thames, and its theatres, galleries and concert venues, while the Tate Britain is within walking distance, too. Closer to home, The Riverside offers locals the chance to indulge on the riverfront, whilst a riverside walk showcases the current development taking place in Nine Elms.

Kennington is one of inner London's best-kept secrets. It’s an enclave of brick houses and pretty squares containing some perfect examples of Georgian architecture. The most famous is the idyllic Cleaver Square, where locals play boules in the summer with merriment aided by the tiny Prince of Wales pub in the corner.

You can enjoy a wide range of cuisines here, from Persian to Eritrean and beyond. A branch of Vietnamese street food chain Aobaba can be found on Walworth Road, while the Portuguese cafes and tapas bars of the South Lam
